<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1194,1975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1339,1363]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName box="[513,605,1340,1363]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis box="[513,605,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(serrated), referring to the serrated edge of the retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1194,1975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1410,1435]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar in the markings to 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon" authorityName="Simon" box="[669,960,1410,1435]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coccineus">
<emphasis box="[669,873,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ilargus coccineus</emphasis>
Simon
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[1033,1281,1410,1434]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Edwards, G. B., Rinaldi, I. M. P. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S. (2005) A review of some South American species of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) described by Mello-Leitao from Brasil, with resolution of the genus Asaphobelis. Biota Neotropica, 5, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2005">
Edwards et al. 
<number box="[1221,1281,1410,1434]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the less elongated body (
<figureCitation box="[635,768,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs 
<number box="[695,768,1446,1470]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="84.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="84.0">84–85</number>
</figureCitation>
); the swollen part at the beginning of the copulatory duct (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1482,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,245,1482,1506]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="91.0">91</number>
</figureCitation>
); the wider and branched embolus, and the serrated retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs 
<number box="[151,225,1518,1542]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="86.5" valueMax="87.0" valueMin="86.0">86–87</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1194,1975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1554,1579]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,409,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[422,525,1554,1578]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00156). Carapace length 
<number box="[985,1023,1554,1578]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.7">1.7</number>
; abdomen length 
<number box="[1219,1258,1554,1578]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.1">2.1</number>
. Chelicera: pale yellow. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[310,446,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs 
<number box="[371,446,1590,1614]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="86.5" valueMax="87.0" valueMin="86.0">86–87</number>
</figureCitation>
): yellowish to yellow brown with gray pigment. Palpal bulb wide; embolus long and coiled for less than a circle, branched from the base; retrolateral tibial apophysis finger-like with dorsal margin serrated; ventral tibial bump absent. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[842,880,1662,1686]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.6">4.6</number>
, II 
<number box="[917,954,1662,1686]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.7">3.7</number>
, III 
<number box="[1003,1041,1662,1686]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.4">4.4</number>
, IV 
<number box="[1089,1127,1662,1686]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.3">4.3</number>
. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1662,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1423,1662,1686]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
): carapace yellowish, with two dark brown wide stripes from anterior eyes to posterior end of carapace; abdomen yellowish, with two lateral dark brown stripes from anterior margin to posterior margin; first pair of legs yellow brown, other legs yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1194,1975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[299,400,1806,1830]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">paratype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00157). Carapace length 
<number box="[872,907,1806,1830]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.2">2.2</number>
(variation 2.0– 
<number box="[1084,1120,1806,1830]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.2">2.2</number>
, n= 
<number box="[1166,1181,1806,1830]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
); abdomen length 
<number box="[1394,1433,1806,1830]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.2">2.2</number>
. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[274,360,1842,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,360,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
): pale yellow. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[806,844,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.6">3.6</number>
, II 
<number box="[883,920,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.3">3.3</number>
, III 
<number box="[969,1007,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.2">4.2</number>
, IV 
<number box="[1056,1095,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.5">4.5</number>
. Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1325,1842,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1293,1325,1842,1866]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="90.0">90</number>
</figureCitation>
): window large; median septum narrow; opening at anterior margin of window. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1156,1878,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1124,1156,1878,1902]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="91.0">91</number>
</figureCitation>
): copulatory duct thick, swollen at the beginning; spermatheca oval. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[849,934,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 91" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1681,1704]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,184,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,179,1688]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 91. Ilargus serratus sp. nov. 84 male holotype, dorsal view; 85 female paratype, dorsal view; 86 male left palp, ventral view; 87 male left palp, retrolateral view; 88 female carapace, dorsal view; 89 female left chelicera, back view; 90 epigynum, ventral view; 91 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 84, 0.5 mm; 85, 1.0 mm; 86 – 91, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209897/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[902,934,1914,1938]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
): paler than that of male, stripes on carapace light orange, stripes on abdomen gray brown, all legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
